# MaintAIn — Project Overview

MaintAIn is a **lightweight, personal web application** for managing recurring apartment/home maintenance tasks. The goal is to prevent forgotten maintenance activities by centralizing all recurring responsibilities in one intuitive system.

## Core Purpose

- Replace scattered notes and calendar reminders with a structured, reliable tracker
- Automatically calculate due dates and highlight overdue or upcoming tasks
- Maintain a full history of completed maintenance activities

## Key User Capabilities

- **Create** recurring tasks with: title, description, category, frequency (weekly / monthly / yearly), and interval (e.g., every 3 months)
- **View** all active tasks with clear status labels: Overdue, Due Soon, Upcoming
- **Edit** tasks (frequency, category, description, etc.)
- **Deactivate or delete** tasks no longer needed
- **Mark tasks as completed** — system auto-generates the next due date
- **Add notes and cost info** when completing a task
- **View completion history** per task
- **Filter** tasks by category, frequency, or status
- **Dashboard** showing: overdue count, due-soon count, completed this month, total active tasks
- **Navigate** between Dashboard and Task Management views
- **Export** task data (optional enhancement)

## Design Principles

- Clarity and predictability over complexity
- Responsive, clean, user-friendly interface
- Lightweight personal tool — not a full property management platform
- Users should feel confident no recurring task will be forgotten
